edu.umd.cs.psl.model.predicate

Class SpecialPredicate

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umd.cs.psl.model.predicate.Predicate
      • edu.umd.cs.psl.model.predicate.FunctionalPredicate
        • edu.umd.cs.psl.model.predicate.SpecialPredicate

  • public abstract class SpecialPredicate
extends FunctionalPredicate
    A commonly used FunctionalPredicate.

    All specific subclasses/instances are provided here.

    A SpecialPredicate should be preferred over a user-made FunctionalPredicate or ExternalFunctionalPredicate because some PSL components can evaluate SpecialPredicates more efficiently. For example, a Database backed by a relational database with an SQL interface might translate some SpecialPredicates directly to SQL.

    The names of SpecialPredicates begin with '#'.
